    detail: "<section class='destination-content'><h2>Overview</h2><p>Mangosteen, often called the 'queen of tropical fruits', is a highly seasonal delicacy in Sri Lanka. Its thick, deep-purple rind encases snow-white, segmented flesh that is tender, juicy and perfumed with a delicate sweetness. Because the tree takes years to bear fruit and the harvest window is short, fresh mangosteen is a prized treat.</p><h2>Why Mangosteen is Special</h2><ul><li>Known worldwide as the 'queen of fruits'</li><li>Delicate, unmatched flavour profile</li><li>Very short seasonal availability makes it precious</li><li>Rich in antioxidants and xanthones</li><li>Prized in traditional medicine</li></ul><h2>How to Enjoy</h2><ul><li>🍑 Peel and eat fresh — the only way to truly savour it</li><li>🍹 Blend into tropical fruit juices</li><li>🍨 Use in fruit salads and light desserts</li><li>🧊 Freeze the flesh for a cool summer treat</li></ul><h2>Season</h2><p><strong>Peak Season:</strong> June – August, with the best fruit in July.</p><p>Fresh mangosteen appears in markets for only a few weeks each year, making it one of the most eagerly awaited seasonal fruits in Sri Lanka. The best specimens come from the wet zone lowlands.</p></section>",
