    detail: "<section class='destination-content'><h2>Overview</h2><p>The king coconut is Sri Lanka's indigenous variety of coconut, distinguished by its vibrant orange shell. Unlike the green coconut used for cooking, the king coconut is grown primarily for its refreshing, slightly sweet water. It is the island's most ubiquitous street drink, with vendors slicing them open with a machete at every corner.</p><h2>Why King Coconut is Special</h2><ul><li>Indigenous to Sri Lanka — not found elsewhere in the world</li><li>Natural isotonic drink, perfect for hydration</li><li>Rich in potassium, electrolytes and minerals</li><li>The ultimate refreshment in Sri Lanka's tropical heat</li><li>Sustainable and biodegradable packaging by nature</li></ul><h2>How to Enjoy</h2><ul><li>🥥 Drink the water straight from the nut</li><li>🍹 Mixed with lime for a refreshing twist</li><li>🍬 King coconut milk used in traditional sweets</li><li>🍨 King coconut ice cream and sorbets</li><li>🌿 King coconut water used in Ayurvedic treatments</li></ul><h2>Season</h2><p><strong>Available:</strong> Year-round, with peak freshness during the dry season (January – March and June – September).</p><p>King coconut trees line roadsides across the island, and the distinctive orange clusters are a defining feature of Sri Lanka's tropical landscape.</p></section>",
