    detail: "<section class='destination-content'><h2>Overview</h2><p>Fresh cashew nuts are one of Sri Lanka's most prized seasonal delicacies, harvested primarily from the dry-zone cashew plantations in the northwestern and northern regions. Unlike roasted or processed cashews, fresh cashews have a creamy, milky texture and a delicate, subtly sweet flavour that is incomparably superior.</p><h2>Why Fresh Cashew is Special</h2><ul><li>Once-a-year harvest makes them a true seasonal treat</li><li>Fresh cashews taste nothing like processed versions</li><li>Sri Lanka produces some of the world's finest cashews</li><li>Rich in healthy fats, protein and minerals</li><li>An important export crop and local delicacy</li></ul><h2>How to Enjoy</h2><ul><li>🥜 Eat raw and fresh — the ultimate way</li><li>🍳 Cashew nut curry (kaju maluwa)</li><li>🍬 Kaju katli and traditional cashew sweets</li><li>🍪 Cashew-based desserts and puddings</li><li>🛒 Buy roasted and salted from local vendors</li></ul><h2>Season</h2><p><strong>Peak Season:</strong> February – April (main harvest), with a smaller crop in August – September.</p><p>The cashew harvest is an important event in the Puttalam, Kurunegala and Kilinochchi districts, where cashew plantations stretch across the dry landscape.</p></section>",
